                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d757">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">861.77/2772: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Warren</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1922-10-19T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 19, 1922—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>121. Your 172, October 17, 2 p.m.</p>
                <p>Consul at Vladivostok who is acting as American representative on the
                    Inter-Allied Committee should also be kept informed of the progress of
                    liquidation and should be instructed to keep in close touch with Stevens in that
                    connection.</p>
                <p>Ask Stevens to telegraph the Department brief comment on the Japanese memorandum
                    and instructions particularly point 4 of the latter concerning proposal to
                    withhold payment of military transportation accounts.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
